-- China Studies Strategic Reserves of 10 Metals, Shanghai Securities Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-02T22:51:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/china-studies-strategic-reserves-for-10-metals-securities-news-reports.html
China is studying the start of
strategic reserves for 10 metals, the Shanghai Securities News
reported today, without citing anyone.  The 10 metals include rare earths, tungsten, antimony,
molybdenum, indium, germanium, gallium, tantalum, zirconium and
tin, according to the Shanghai-based newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 jliu42@bloomberg.net  